{{italic title}} The '''''Kakinomoto no Ason Hitomaro Kashū''''' (柿本朝臣人麿歌集, "Collection of Poems/Songs by [[Kakinomoto no Ason Hitomaro]]") or '''''Hitomaro Kashū''''' (人麿歌集) is a [[lost work|lost]] collection of ''[[waka (poetry)|waka]]'' poems that served as a source for the compilers of the ''[[Man'yōshū]]''. There is some disagreement among scholars as to which poems included in the surviving ''Man'yōshū'' originally came from the ''Hitomaro Kashū'', but it is between 364 and 370. Scholars have speculated on the nature of the original ''Hitomaro Kashū'' based on the surviving fragmentary and disjointed evidence.
== Authorship, compiler, date and structure == The compiler of the ''Kakinomoto no Ason Hitomaro Kashū'',{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=684}} (hereafter the ''Hitomaro Kashū''{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=685}}) as well as its date{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=684}} and number of books are all unknown.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=684}} While the text itself does not survive,{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=685}} scholars have been able to guess as to the form the work probably took based on the portions of the late eighth-century ''[[Man'yōshū]]'' that incorporate a large number of its poems.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=685}} Poems attributed to it were incorporated into books 2, 3, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12, 13 and 14 of the later anthology.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1pp=684-685}}
== Contents == Depending on whether the ''Man'yōshū'' poems numbered 146 (book 2), 1715, 1716, 1717, 1718 and 1718 (all book 9) were originally taken from the ''Hitomaro Kashū'', the number of poems varies from 364 to 370.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=685}} {{illm|Mizue Aso|ja|阿蘇瑞枝}}, in her article on the work for the ''[[Nihon Koten Bungaku Daijiten]]'', gave the figure of 365.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=685}} These consist of two ''[[chōka]]'', 35 ''[[sedōka]]'', and 328 ''[[tanka]]''.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=685}} (All the disputed poems are ''tanka'', so this figure would vary between 327 and 333.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=685}}) [[Susumu Nakanishi]], in his ''[[Man'yōshū Jiten]]'', gave a figure of 369.{{sfnm|1a1=Nakanishi|1y=1985|1p=221}}
=== Script format of ''tanka'' === The ''tanka'' attributed by the compiler(s) of the ''Man'yōshū'' to the ''Hitomaro Kashū'' are divided into two categories based on how distinctly particles and auxiliary words are represented therein.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=585}} The poems that carefully indicate these words are called ''hi-ryakutai-ka'' (非略体歌),{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=585}} and those that do not are called''ryakutai-ka'' (略体歌).{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=585}} Roughly 127 poems fall into the former group, with roughly 196 in the latter,{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=585}} though opinions on which poems are which group differ between various scholars.{{sfnm|1a1=Aso|1y=1983|1p=585}}
